    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. DELANEY:H.R. 2981.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 4, Clause 1``The Times, Places and Manner of holding Elections forSenators and Representatives, shall be prescribed in eachState by the Legislature thereof; but the Congress may at anytime by Law make or alter such Regulations, except as to thePlaces of chusing Senators.''[Page H5049]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
